From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 05:50:07 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: emit the current phase's text base in _TEXT_BASE

_TEXT_BASE holds CONFIG_TEXT_BASE, u-boot proper's link address, even in an
SPL or TPL build whose code is linked at CONFIG_SPL_TEXT_BASE /
CONFIG_TPL_TEXT_BASE. Nothing in SPL/TPL reads _TEXT_BASE -- relocate_code()
and the crt0 relocation that consume it are compiled only for u-boot proper
(!CONFIG_XPL_BUILD) -- so the stale value is normally dead data and the bug
goes unnoticed.

It stops being dead data for CONFIG_ROCKCHIP_MASKROM_IMAGE. That image places
the SPL binary at file offset 0, and _TEXT_BASE lands at offset 8, where the
arm64 image header carries the load address. The RK3576 BootROM reads that
field to place the CODE472 download: with CONFIG_TEXT_BASE (8 MiB above the
SPL's real base on rk3576) it loads the SPL where the code was not linked to
run, faults before U-Boot ever starts, and also puts the appended FIT 8 MiB
off from SPL_LOAD_FIT_ADDRESS.

Use CONFIG_VAL(TEXT_BASE), which resolves to the text base of the phase
actually being built, so each stage's _TEXT_BASE matches its link address.
U-Boot proper is unchanged.

Signed-off-by: gregordinary <33880035+gregordinary@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 arch/arm/cpu/armv8/start.S | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm/cpu/armv8/start.S b/arch/arm/cpu/armv8/start.S
index 40c342e9..c0aa81c5 100644
--- a/arch/arm/cpu/armv8/start.S
+++ b/arch/arm/cpu/armv8/start.S
@@ -35,7 +35,7 @@ _start:
 
 .globl	_TEXT_BASE
 _TEXT_BASE:
-	.quad	CONFIG_TEXT_BASE
+	.quad	CONFIG_VAL(TEXT_BASE)
 
 /*
  * These are defined in the linker script.
